---

Type 1 vs Type 2

Feature	Type 1	Type 2

History	Lost	Preserved
Update	Overwrite	Insert new row
Storage	Small	Larger
Complexity	Simple	Higher
Historical Reporting	Incorrect	Correct
---

Common Interview Questions

Q1. What is SCD Type 2?

Preserves historical dimension changes by creating new rows.
---

Q2. Why surrogate key important in Type 2?
Allows multiple historical records for same business key.
---
Q3. Why not overwrite?
Would lose historical accuracy.
---

Q4. Which columns commonly used?
effective_date
end_date
